headlines.description: Mitchell Trubisky threw a go-ahead, 3-yard touchdown pass to David Montgomery with 2:17 left, lifting the Chicago Bears to a 24-20 win over the slumping Detroit Lions on Thursday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trubisky’s 3rd TD pass lifts Bears to 24-20 win over Lions

video.headline: Trubisky, Bears battle past Lions in Thanksgiving thriller

headlines.description: John Brown became the first Buffalo receiver to throw a touchdown pass immediately after quarterback Josh Allen turned a fourth-down fumble into a first down, and the Bills went on to beat the Dallas Cowboys 26-15 on Thursday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trick TD sparks Bills in 26-15 Thanksgiving win over Cowboys

video.headline: Cowboys' costly turnovers seal Bills' win

events.name: New Orleans Saints at Atlanta Falcons

headlines.description: Taysom Hill blocked a punt to set up his 3-yard touchdown catch, later scored on a 30-yard run and the New Orleans Saints clinched their third straight NFC South title by beating the Atlanta Falcons 26-18 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Saints beat Falcons to clinch third straight NFC South title
